      "correct": "Great read at speed. No arrows, tight window — you trusted the short closeout and shot it.",
      "partial": "The drive scores sometimes, but at this speed the open shot is the play. Trust the cushion.",
      "wrong": "Too slow. Short closeout means shoot — decide the instant the ball lands."
